Ronaldo Awarded Golden Ball Title 
Brazilian striker Ronaldo has won the award of the prestigious Golden
Ball European Footballer of the Year given by the France Football
magazine for 1996-97, according to sources at the Confederations Cup
here on Friday.
The Inter Milan international got most votes ahead of Real Madrid's
Yugoslav striker Pedrag Mijatovic and Juventus' French star Zinedine
Zidane.
Arsenal's Dutch forward Dennis Bergkamp finished fourth, with Ronaldo's
compatriot, Real Madrid wingback Roberto Carlos fifth.
The decision will officially be announced Monday evening by the
magazine.
